Comment 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E5EFFB3FEF4FECFDB6BFEAF" authorityName="ERICHSON" authorityYear="1840" box="[333,534,308,329]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Philonthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turbidus">
<emphasis id="B90819228E5EFFB3FEF4FECFDB6BFEAF" box="[333,534,308,329]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Philonthus turbidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in the southern Palaearctic, the Afrotropical, 
<collectingRegion id="49B80BD28E5EFFB3FEBBFEAAD825FE81" box="[258,344,337,359]" country="Saudi Arabia" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Oriental</collectingRegion>
, and Nearctic regions (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E5EFFB3FDE1FEAADB83FE81" author="SMETANA A" box="[600,766,337,359]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" pagination="505 - 698" refId="ref7869" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Staphylinidae, subfamilies Omaliinae - Dasycerinae, Phloeocharinae - Apaticinae, Piestinae - Staphylininae, pp. 237 - 272, 329 - 495, 505 - 698. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. II. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. - Stenstrup, Apollo Books: 942 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA 2004</bibRefCitation>
). It had been reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E5EFFB3FF1AFE95D855FE62" box="[163,296,366,388]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E5EFFB3FEF7FE95D892FE62" author="COIFFAIT H" box="[334,495,366,388]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" pagination="162 - 180" refId="ref7416" refString="COIFFAIT H. (1979): Insects of Saudi Arabia. Coleoptera: Fam. Staphylinidae, Subfam. Xantholinae [sic], Staphylininae, Paederinae, Oxytelinae, Aleocharinae. - Fauna of Saudi Arabia 1: 162 - 180." type="journal article" year="1979">COIFFAIT (1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E5EFFB3FE43FE95DB53FE62" author="COIFFAIT H" box="[506,558,366,388]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" pagination="236 - 242" refId="ref7460" refString="COIFFAIT H. (1981): Insects of Saudi Arabia. Coleoptera: Fam. Staphylinidae, Subfam. Xantholininae, Staphylininae, Paederinae, Oxytelinae, Aleocharinae (Part 2). - Fauna of Saudi Arabia 3: 236 - 242." type="journal article" year="1981">1981</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E5EFFB3FDDFFE95DA65FE62" author="GUSAROV V" box="[614,792,366,388]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" pagination="277 - 290" refId="ref7600" refString="GUSAROV V. I. (1997): Staphylinids (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) from Saudi Arabia and Oman. - Fauna of Saudi Arabia 16: 277 - 290." type="journal article" year="1997">GUSAROV (1997)</bibRefCitation>
.
